#title[How to Reverse Park]

#let not-a-problem = [
  Actually, as soon as I got the license, I drove about 3 hours (with an
  experienced driver on the copilot seat) on an expressway on a rainy day, and I
  was not nervous at all.
]
About two months ago, I had finally got my driving license. Driving on the road
was not a problem for me#footnote(not-a-problem), but parking was quite a
challenge.

Parking spaces in reality are often much tighter than the ones in the driving
test, and there may be other obstacles around, such as pedestrians, bicycles,
and other cars. One has to be really careful and precise when parking, for
safety reasons.

